Such communications shall be through thecompany’s newsletters.Other communication from external interested parties received on board a ship or by a company office should be referred to theManagement Representative. Receipt of such a communication shall be recorded, discussed during the Quarterly ManagementReview, responded to as decided and action taken recorded under his responsibility.Lessons learnt from incidents shall be shared with industry groups such as classification societies, professional institutes, equipmentmanufacturers and oil majors, as appropriate. The intent of communication to outside interests is to avoid misinterpretation /misinformation.Press Releases shall be put on the company website as and when relevant10.2.2COMMUNICATION ON ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUESThe HSEQA Department has primary responsibility for responding to any enquiries and other communication from external sources onmatters concerning environmental aspects and environmental management systems.Enquiries and other communication (received by mail, fax, telephone, in person, etc.) from external parties concerning theEnvironmental Management System or Environmental performance shall be referred to the DPA to determine the necessaryresponse.Environmental complaints received on board should be processed using the nonconformance system. As well as receiving verbal orwritten complaints, environmental remarks on the following may be deemed to be a complaint:1) Charterer’s Communications2) Complaints from Port Authority / Pressure Groups /Private Citizen3) Terminal Feedback4) OVID / OSVIS / IMCA ReportsThe Company uses a number of mechanisms to ensure effective communication with relevant interested parties. These mechanismsinclude:1) Regulatory filings (such as permit applications and reports);2) Formal and informal discussions with regulators, Class representatives, and community representatives.3) Newsletters and Company Publications4) Company website5) Soliciting views of interested parties through Surveys and informal meetings with representatives of external groups
